{"title_page": "2009\u201310 Olympiacos F.C. season", "text_new": "{{Update|date=October 2010}}\n{{Infobox football club season\n|club               = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|season             = 2009\u201310\n|manager            = [[Temuri Ketsbaia]]<br>(until 25 November 2009)<br>[[Zico]]<br>(until 1 March 2010)<br>[[Bo\u017eidar Bandovi\u0107]]\n|chairman           = [[Sokratis Kokkalis]]\n|league             = [[2009\u201310 Super League Greece|Super League Greece]]\n|league result      = 2nd in regular season (5th in [[2009\u201310 Super League Greece#Play-offs|play-offs]])\n|cup1               = [[2009\u201310 Greek Football Cup|Greek Cup]]\n|cup1 result        = [[2009\u201310 Greek Football Cup#Fourth round|Fourth round]]\n|cup2               = [[2009\u201310 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]]\n|cup2 result        = [[2009\u201310 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|Round of 16]]\n|league topscorer   = \n|season topscorer   = \n|highest attendance = 31,059 vs [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]<br>(29 November 2009)\n|lowest attendance  = 16,056 vs [[Kavala F.C.|Kavala]]<br>(12 September 2009)\n|average attendance = 21,341\n|pattern_la1        = _olympiacosfc0910h\n|pattern_b1         = _olympiacosfc0910h\n|pattern_ra1        = \n|pattern_sh1        = _olympiacosfc0910h\n|pattern_so1        = _5redstripes\n|leftarm1           = FF0000\n|body1              = FF0000\n|rightarm1          = FF0000\n|shorts1            = FF0000\n|socks1             = FFFFFF\n|pattern_la2        = _olympiacosfc0910a\n|pattern_b2         = _olympiacosfc0910a\n|pattern_ra2        = \n|pattern_sh2        = _olympiacosfc0910a\n|pattern_so2        = _atleticomg14a\n|leftarm2           = 000000\n|body2              = 000000\n|rightarm2          = 000000\n|shorts2            = 000000\n|socks2             = 000000\n|pattern_la3        = _thinredborder\n|pattern_b3         = _olympiacosfc0910t\n|pattern_ra3        = _thinredborder\n|pattern_sh3        = _olympiacosfc0910t\n|pattern_so3        = _olympiacosfc0910t\n|leftarm3           = FFFFFF\n|body3              = FFFFFF\n|rightarm3          = FFFFFF\n|shorts3            = FFFFFF\n|socks3             = FFFFFF\n|prevseason         = [[2008\u201309 Olympiacos F.C. season|2008\u201309]]\n|nextseason         = [[2010\u201311 Olympiacos F.C. season|2010\u201311]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2009\u201310 season''' was '''[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]'''' 51st consecutive season in the [[Superleague Greece]]. Olympiacos finished 2nd in the regular season of the Greek SuperLeague and ranked last at the play-off games, resulting in a 5th place at the League, the worst position of team's recent seasons. Olympiacos also participated in UEFA Champions League 09-10, and managed to qualify to the knock-stage (round of 16). They lost twice from French side Bordeaux, 3-1 on aggregate. \n\nThis season was the last season with [[Sokratis Kokkalis]] as chairman of the club. The 5th league position as well as the team's low level of spectacle created a disappointing atmosphere, resulting in Kokkalis's decision to leave the club after two decades of constant presence.\n\n==Events==\n<!-- Add any important events like manager changes or transfers, but not match results, to this section. Do not forget to source your additions! -->\n* 27 May 2009: Former [[Georgia (country)|Georgian]] international player [[Temuri Ketsbaia]] is appointed coach, replacing [[Ernesto Valverde]] from [[Spain]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.olympiacos.org/index.html?lang=en#/Article/25949/|title=Press release|date=27 May 2009|publisher=[[Olympiacos F.C.]] official website|accessdate=5 July 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090629194254/http://www.olympiacos.org/index.html?lang=en#/Article/25949/|archivedate=2009-06-29|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* 19 June 2009: [[Antonios Nikopolidis]], [[Dudu Cearense|Dudu]], and [[Luciano Galletti]] are appointed captains for the 2009\u201310 season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.olympiacos.org/index.html?lang=en#/Article/25991/|title=Press release|date=19 June 2009|publisher=[[Olympiacos F.C.]] official website|accessdate=5 July 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090629194254/http://www.olympiacos.org/index.html?lang=en#/Article/25991/|archivedate=2009-06-29|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* 23 June 2009: [[Sweden|Swedish]] international [[Olof Mellberg]] is signed from [[Serie A]] sides [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.olympiacos.org/index.html?lang=en#/Article/26001/|title=Press release|date=23 June 2009|publisher=[[Olympiacos F.C.]] official website|accessdate=5 July 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090629194254/http://www.olympiacos.org/index.html?lang=en#/Article/26001/|archivedate=2009-06-29|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Matt Derbyshire]] is also signed from [[Premier League]] team [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.olympiacos.org/index.html?lang=en#/Article/26003/|title=Press release|date=23 June 2009|publisher=[[Olympiacos F.C.]] official website|accessdate=5 July 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090629194254/http://www.olympiacos.org/index.html?lang=en#/Article/26003/|archivedate=2009-06-29|url-status=dead}}</ref> after previously being on loan with Olympiacos.\n* 15 September 2009: Manager [[Temuri Ketsbaia]] is sacked despite not conceding a single goal in his time at the club he was replaced with [[Bo\u017eidar Bandovi\u0107]] who hasn't impressed at Olympiacos.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.olympiakos.gr/index.html?lang=en |title=Archived copy |access-date=2010-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100407092425/http://www.olympiakos.gr/index.html?lang=en#/MatchReport/2661/ |archive-date=2010-04-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Teams and players 2009\u201310==\n\n===First team===\n:''Roster update: 01 August 2009''<ref name=\"First Team Players \">{{cite web |url=http://olympiakos.gr/index.html?lang=en#/Football/Players/ |