iacos and AEK rivalry|6]]\n|date       = 19 May 2010\n|time       = 21:15\n|team1      = [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n|score      = 2\u20131\n|report     = https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2010/05/19/greece/super-league/aek-athens-fc/olympiakos-cfp/931171/?ICID=PL_MS_09\n|team2      = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|goals1     = [[Kostas Manolas|Manolas]] {{goal|6}}<br />[[Ismael Blanco|Blanco]] {{goal|54}}\n|goals2     = [[Yiannis Papadopoulos|Y. Papadopoulos]] {{goal|10}}\n|stadium    = [[Olympic Stadium (Athens)|Olympic Stadium]]\n|location   = [[Athens]]\n|attendance = 14,738\n|referee    = Tasos Kakos\n|result     = L\n}}\n\n==Greek Cup==\n\n===Fourth round===\n''All times at [[Eastern European Time|EET]]''\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date       = 27 October 2009\n|time       = 17:00\n|team1      = [[Panserraikos F.C.|Panserraikos]]\n|score      = 3\u20131\n|report     = \n|team2      = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|goals1     = [[Leozinho]] {{goal|16}}<br>[[Stefanos Athanasiadis|Athanasiadis]] {{goal|52}}<br>[[Lucas Rimoldi|Rimoldi]] {{goal|84}}\n|goals2     = [[Kostas Mitroglou|Mitroglou]] {{goal|66}}\n|stadium    = [[Serres Municipal Stadium]]\n|location   = [[Serres]]\n|attendance = \n|referee    = \n|result     = L\n}}\n\n==UEFA Champions League==\n\n===Third qualifying round===\n''All times at [[Eastern European Time|EET]]''\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date       = 29 July 2009\n|time       = 21:00\n|team1      = [[\u0160K Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]] {{Flag icon|SVK}}\n|score      = 0\u20132\n|report     = [http://www.uefa.com/competitions/ucl/fixturesresults/round=2000026/match=2000315/index.html (Report)]\n|team2      = {{Flag icon|GRE}} [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|goals1     = \n|goals2     = [[Avraam Papadopoulos|Papadopoulos]] {{goal|2}}<br>[[Leonardo de Jesus Geraldo|Leonardo]] {{goal|22}}\n|stadium    = [[Teheln\u00e9 pole]]\n|location   = [[Bratislava]], [[Slovakia]]\n|attendance = 21,250<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/news/2009/July/30/olympiakos-too-strong-for-slovan-bratislava/|title=Olympiakos too strong for Slovan Bratislava|publisher=Soccerway|date=2009-07-30|accessdate=2009-10-28}}</ref>\n|referee    = Claudio Circhetta ([[Swiss Football Association|Switzerland]])\n|result     = W\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date       = 5 August 2009\n|time       = 21:45\n|team1      = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] {{Flag icon|GRE}}\n|score      = 2\u20130\n|report     = [http://www.uefa.com/competitions/ucl/fixturesresults/round=2000026/match=2000330/index.html (Report)]\n|team2      = {{Flag icon|SVK}} [[\u0160K Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]]\n|goals1     = [[Enzo Maresca|Maresca]] {{goal|35}}<br>[[Diogo Luis Santo|Diogo]] {{goal|56}}\n|goals2     = \n|stadium    = [[Karaiskakis Stadium]]\n|location   = [[Piraeus]], [[Greece]]\n|attendance = 26,137<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.olympiacos.org/#/Article/26177/ |script-title=el:\u039f\u03bb\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2-\u03a3\u03bb\u03cc\u03b2\u03b1\u03bd \u039c\u03c0\u03c1\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03c3\u03bb\u03ac\u03b2\u03b1\u03c2 2\u20130 |language=Greek |publisher=Olympiacos official website |date=2009-08-05 |accessdate=2009-10-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150810065503/http://www.olympiacos.org/ |archivedate=2015-08-10 }}</ref>\n|referee    = [[Konrad Plautz]] ([[Austrian Football Association|Austria]])\n|result     = W\n}}\n''Olympiacos won 4\u20130 on aggregate.''\n\n===Play-off round===\n''All times at [[Eastern European Time|EET]]''\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date       = 18 August 2009\n|time       = 21:45\n|team1      = [[FC Sheriff Tiraspol|Sheriff Tiraspol]] {{Flag icon|MDA}}\n|score      = 0\u20132\n|report     = [http://www.uefa.com/competitions/ucl/fixturesresults/round=2000027/match=2000344/report=rp.html (Report)]\n|team2      = {{Flag icon|GRE}} [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|goals1     = \n|goals2     = [[Dudu Cearense|Dudu]] {{goal|46}}<br>[